content:
-9/11 Memorial- 
The names of all 2,983 victims are engraved on the 152 bronze panels surrounding the pools, arranged by where individuals were on the day of the attacks, so coworkers and people on the same flight are memorialized together.
"Never Forget"

content:
Auschwitz II-Birkenau. Concentration camp.
Prisoners were brought to Auschwitz crammed in wretched conditions into goods or cattle wagons near a railway station or at one of several dedicated trackside ramps.
Arriving at this ramp meant a 2.5 km journey to Auschwitz II and the gas chambers.
"In memoriam"
